Image 48
The [Royal Stewart tartan](/Royal_Stewart_tartan). It is also the personal tartan of Queen [Elizabeth II](/Elizabeth_II). Tartan is used in clothing, such as skirts and scarves, and has also appeared on tins of Scottish [shortbread](/Shortbread). A pattern that speaks of heritage, tradition, and perhaps, a touch of marketing genius. (from [Culture of the United Kingdom](/Culture_of_the_United_Kingdom) )

