[Queen Victoria](/Queen_Victoria) in her [white wedding](/White_wedding) dress with Prince Albert on their return from the marriage service at St James's Palace, London, 10 February 1840. A moment of royal romance, soon to be overshadowed by the weight of empire. (from [Culture of the United Kingdom](/Culture_of_the_United_Kingdom) )

