Statue of a [tripod](/Tripod_(The_War_of_the_Worlds)) from [The War of the Worlds](/The_War_of_the_Worlds) in Woking, England, the hometown of author [H. G. Wells](/H._G._Wells). The book is a seminal depiction of a conflict between mankind and an [extraterrestrial](/Extraterrestrials_in_fiction) race. A rather stark reminder that even quaint English towns can inspire cosmic dread. (from [Culture of the United Kingdom](/Culture_of_the_United_Kingdom) )

