[Bodiam Castle](/Bodiam_Castle) is a 14th-century [moated](/Moat) [castle](/Castle) in East Sussex. Today there are thousands of [castles throughout the UK](/Castles_in_Great_Britain_and_Ireland). Defensive architecture, or just an elaborate way to keep the neighbours out? (from [Culture of the United Kingdom](/Culture_of_the_United_Kingdom) )

