The Christmas Pantomime 1890. [Pantomime](/Pantomime) plays a prominent role in British culture during the Christmas and New Year season. A theatrical tradition, often involving cross-dressing, audience participation, and questionable puns. (from [Culture of the United Kingdom](/Culture_of_the_United_Kingdom) )

