Two of the current [Ravens of the Tower of London](/Ravens_of_the_Tower_of_London). The ravens' presence is traditionally believed to protect the [Crown](/The_Crown) and the tower; a superstition holds that "if the [Tower of London](/Tower_of_London) ravens are lost or fly away, the Crown will fall and Britain with it". A rather heavy burden for a few birds. (from [Culture of the United Kingdom](/Culture_of_the_United_Kingdom) )

