[Westminster Abbey](/Westminster_Abbey) is an example of [English Gothic architecture](/English_Gothic_architecture). Since 1066, when [William the Conqueror](/William_the_Conqueror) was crowned, the coronations of British monarchs have been held here. A place of solemn ceremony, where centuries of history are literally carved in stone. (from [Culture of the United Kingdom](/Culture_of_the_United_Kingdom) )

