Ice dancers [Torvill and Dean](/Torvill_and_Dean) in 2011. Their historic gold medal-winning performance at the [1984 Winter Olympics](/1984_Winter_Olympics) was watched by a British television audience of more than 24 million people. A moment of pure grace and national triumph on ice. (from [Culture of the United Kingdom](/Culture_of_the_United_Kingdom) )

