[City of London](/City_of_London)
Photo credit: [David Iliff](/User:Diliff)

The [City of London](/City_of_London) skyline, as viewed toward the northwest from the rather elevated vantage point of the top floor viewing platform of [London City Hall](/City_Hall_(London)), perched on the southern side of the venerable [River Thames](/River_Thames). One must not, under any circumstances, confuse this historical square mile with the sprawling [London metropolitan area](/London) as a whole. The City itself covers a mere 1.12 sq mi (2.90 km²) and, alongside its equally historic counterpart, [Westminster](/Westminster), forms the ancient core of London, around which the entire modern [conurbation](/Conurbation) has inconveniently, yet inevitably, expanded.

