Image 2

[Broadway Tower](/Broadway_Tower,_Worcestershire)
Photo credit: [Newton2](/User:Newton2)/[YFB](/User:Yummifruitbat)

[Broadway Tower](/Broadway_Tower,_Worcestershire) stands as a rather charming [folly](/Folly), strategically located near the picturesque village of [Broadway, Worcestershire](/Broadway,_Worcestershire), nestled within the heart of [England](/England). It occupies one of the highest points of the rolling [Cotswolds], its base an impressive 1,024 feet (312 m) above sea level, with the tower itself reaching a further 55 feet (17 m) into the sky. On one of those rare, truly clear days, a visitor from its summit can supposedly discern no fewer than thirteen [counties of England](/Counties_of_England). A rather grand view, if you have the patience for it.

