[Gibraltar](/Gibraltar)
Map credit: Eric Gaba/[Jeff Dahl](/User:Jeff_Dahl)

A detailed map of [Gibraltar](/Gibraltar), a steadfast [British overseas territory](/British_overseas_territory) located rather precariously near the southernmost tip of the [Iberian Peninsula](/Iberian_Peninsula), proudly overlooking the strategic choke-point of the [Strait of Gibraltar](/Strait_of_Gibraltar). The territory shares a singular, often contentious, border with [Spain](/Spain) to its north. Historically, Gibraltar has served as an absolutely vital base for the [British Armed Forces](/British_Armed_Forces), and it remains the site of a significant [Royal Navy](/Royal_Navy) base, a persistent symbol of British influence in a rather sensitive geopolitical region.

