Image 6

[London King's Cross railway station](/London_King%27s_Cross_railway_station)
Photo: [Colin](/User:Colin)

The expansive western departures concourse of [London King's Cross railway station](/London_King%27s_Cross_railway_station), captured with a sweeping perspective through a [fisheye lens](/Fisheye_lens). This magnificent semi-circular concourse, a marvel of modern design, was conceived by [John McAslan](/John_McAslan), brought to fruition by [Vinci](/Vinci_(construction)), and finally completed in March 2012. Its primary purpose, rather prosaically, is to accommodate the significantly increased passenger flows that modern rail travel demands, and to provide a far greater degree of seamless integration between the intercity, suburban, and crucial [Underground](/London_Underground) sections of this bustling station. A rather elegant solution to the perennial problem of too many people wanting to go somewhere, all at once.

[More featured pictures](/Portal:United_Kingdom/Featured_picture)

