Image 9

[Windsor Castle](/Windsor_Castle)
Photo credit: [Diliff](/User:Diliff)

The magnificent [quadrangle](/Quadrangle_(architecture)) of [Windsor Castle](/Windsor_Castle), proudly standing as one of the principal official residences of the [British monarch](/Monarchy_of_the_United_Kingdom). To the far left, one can discern the State Apartments, while at the very end of the quadrangle lie the Private Apartments, the preferred weekend abode of Queen [Elizabeth II](/Elizabeth_II) during her reign. On the right, the South Wing completes this architectural ensemble. This venerable structure, located at [Windsor](/Windsor,_Berkshire) within the rather verdant [English county](/Counties_of_England) of [Berkshire](/Berkshire), holds the distinction of being the largest inhabited [castle](/Castle) in the entire world. Furthermore, its history dates back to the era of [William the Conqueror](/William_the_Conqueror), solidifying its claim as the oldest castle in continuous occupation. A rather enduring monument to royal longevity, then.

[More featured pictures](/Portal:United_Kingdom/Featured_picture)

