Image 10

[Charles II of England](/Charles_II_of_England)
Painting: [John Michael Wright](/John_Michael_Wright) or studio

[Charles II of England](/Charles_II_of_England) (1630–1685) reigned as king of [England](/Kingdom_of_England), [Scotland](/Kingdom_of_Scotland), and [Ireland](/Kingdom_of_Ireland). His tenure as king of Scotland commenced in 1649, immediately following [his father's execution](/Charles_I_of_England), though this reign was rather abruptly cut short when he was deposed by the formidable [Oliver Cromwell](/Oliver_Cromwell) in 1651. His more enduring reign as king of England, Scotland, and Ireland began with the jubilant [restoration of the monarchy](/Restoration_(1660)) in 1660, lasting until his death. On the international stage, Charles found himself embroiled in the rather costly [Second](/Second_Anglo-Dutch_War) and [Third Anglo-Dutch Wars](/Third_Anglo-Dutch_War), conflicts that did little for the royal coffers. Domestically, Charles made a rather bold, if ultimately unsuccessful, attempt to introduce greater [religious freedom](/Freedom_of_religion) for both Catholics and Protestant [dissenters](/Dissenter) with his 1672 [Royal Declaration of Indulgence](/Declaration_of_Indulgence_(1672)). However, the ever-watchful [English Parliament](/English_Parliament) rather forcefully compelled him to withdraw it, demonstrating the shifting balance of power.

[More featured pictures](/Portal:United_Kingdom/Featured_picture)

