Image 14

[Felbrigge Psalter](/Felbrigge_Psalter)
Book credit: Anne de Felbrigge

The [Felbrigge Psalter](/Felbrigge_Psalter), an exquisitely crafted [illuminated manuscript](/Illuminated_manuscript) [Psalter], holds the distinction of being the oldest book from [England] known to feature an [embroidered](/Embroidery) [bookbinding]. The intricate needlework adorning this mid-thirteenth century manuscript is generally dated to the early fourteenth century, which places it more than a full century earlier than the next oldest surviving embroidered binding. Both the artistic design and the meticulous execution depicting the [Annunciation] are of an exceptionally high quality, a testament to the skill of its creator. The cover itself is fashioned with [linen] and [gold](/Gold_thread) thread on linen, with a later leather binding edge added for durability. A rather precious artefact, preserving both sacred text and delicate craftsmanship.

