Did you know -
• load new batch

• ... that, before [same-sex unions were legally recognised in the UK](/Same-sex_marriage_in_the_United_Kingdom), the [London Partnership Register](/London_Partnership_Register) allowed nearly 1,000 couples to celebrate their relationships? A rather forward-thinking initiative, predating national recognition, allowing people to formalize their affections in a city that, for all its faults, has always had a knack for finding a way.

• ... that Dublin property developer [Harry Crosbie](/Harry_Crosbie) received an [OBE](/Order_of_the_British_Empire) from the [British ambassador to Ireland](/List_of_ambassadors_of_the_United_Kingdom_to_Ireland), partly for [entertaining Elizabeth II](/State_visit_by_Elizabeth_II_to_the_Republic_of_Ireland) with his showbiz contacts? Because nothing bridges diplomatic divides quite like a good show and a bit of national recognition.

• ... that a £142 wine fridge was [smuggled into Downing Street on 11 December 2020](/Timeline_of_Partygate), during the height of the [COVID-19 lockdown in the United Kingdom](/COVID-19_lockdown_in_the_United_Kingdom)? A rather stark illustration of priorities during a national crisis, wouldn't you say? Some things, apparently, are truly essential.

• ... that former [Scottish Conservative](/Scottish_Conservatives) leader [Ruth Davidson](/Ruth_Davidson) said that she would swim in [Loch Ness](/Loch_Ness) naked if the [SNP](/Scottish_National_Party) won more than 50 seats at the [2019 United Kingdom general election](/2019_United_Kingdom_general_election)? A bold, if rather chilling, promise, thankfully not put to the test, sparing both the public and potentially Nessie herself.

• ... that when [Sarah Jane Baker](/Sarah_Jane_Baker) was released after 30 years, she was the United Kingdom's longest serving transgender prisoner? A rather sobering statistic, highlighting the long and often difficult journey towards recognition and justice.

• ... that [Liz Shore](/Liz_Shore)'s nomination to be [Chief Medical Officer](/Chief_Medical_Officers_(United_Kingdom)) of the United Kingdom was vetoed by [Margaret Thatcher](/Margaret_Thatcher) because of Shore's husband's political affiliation? A clear demonstration that even in matters of public health, politics, unfortunately, often finds a way to interfere.

